	<fdd:identificationAndDescription>
		<fdd:fullName>Matroska File Format with LPCM Audio Encoding</fdd:fullName>
		<fdd:keywords>
			<fdd:keyword>audio formats</fdd:keyword>
			<fdd:keyword>recorded sound formats</fdd:keyword>
			<fdd:keyword>video formats</fdd:keyword>
		</fdd:keywords>
		<fdd:description>
			<p>
				<a href="https://www.matroska.org/technical/basics.html">Matroska</a> file containing  <fddLink id="fdd000011">LPCM</fddLink> audio encoding.</p>. <p>Supported encodings are declared via the unique <i>Codec ID</i> in the <a href="https://www.matroska.org/technical/codec_specs.html">Matroska Codec Mappings</a>. Note that Matroska does not have a specific Codec ID for LPCM encoding. Instead, Matroska lists Codec ID for PCM Integer Big Endian (A_PCM/INT/BIG),  PCM Integer Little Endian (A_PCM/INT/LIT) and Floating Point, IEEE compatible (A_PCM/FLOAT/IEEE). <a href="../contact_format.shtml">Comments welcome</a>.</p>
		</fdd:description>
		<fdd:shortDescription>Matroska file containing an audio essence encoded as Linear Pulse Code Modulated (LPCM)</fdd:shortDescription>
		<fdd:productionPhase>Middle state, used for storage or archiving</fdd:productionPhase>
